# Code Conventions

## Components

- Functional components + hooks ONLY (no class components)
- Props interface: `{ComponentName}Props`
- Named exports only (no default exports)
- Colocated tests: `ComponentName.test.tsx`

## TypeScript

- Strict mode — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for simple types
- Import types: `import type { X } from "..."`

## Files

- kebab-case for files: `element-utils.ts`
- PascalCase for components: `LayerUI.tsx`

## How to verify

1. Run `yarn test:typecheck` — no TypeScript errors; strict mode violations absent
2. Run `yarn fix` — no formatting or linting issues remain
3. Search for `class ` components, `export default`, or `interface ` for simple types — none introduced
4. Confirm new files follow naming conventions: kebab-case for utilities, PascalCase for components
5. Verify new component props types follow the `{ComponentName}Props` naming pattern
